  "text": "Legislation and driving education are other safety countermeasures which may take advantage of the results presented in this study. For instance, phone interaction could be prohibited on certain road areas (e.g., curved stretches of road or approaches to traffic lights in unexpected locations) where the driver would be most likely to face difficulties while multitasking. These data were collected in Sweden, where there is no legislation against mobile phone use while driving. It is possible that a ban (full or conditional) would affect mobile phone use while driving [CITATION_1] . In addition, driver education could include making new drivers aware of safe glance behavior in different driving contexts.",
